If you are moving away from the legacy HostScope, you might want to skip 
ahead to a &#39;deciding&#39; (DecideRule) based scope, as all prior scopes are 
now discouraged.

This is the default in 1.12+, but also was available as the 
&#39;deciding-default&#39; profile earlier.

Those defaults should do what you want -- if you remove the 
&#39;TransclusionDecideRule&#39;. That&#39;s what brings in inline resources 
(accessed via &#39;E&#39;mbed, &#39;X&#39;speculative, &#39;R&#39;edirection hops) that would 
not otherwise be ruled-in.

- Gordon @ IA

